title: 820-00165-a fan spin, no chime, no display
message:
Liquid spill, corrosion around u6100, everywhere else looks perfect.
Originally no boot, after removing u6100, cleaning pin 7 and replacing, it turns on, has vcore, gets warm, fan spins normally, will turn on and off with power button.
No chime no display, no backlight

u6100 replaced from donor board - twice.
diode mode with u6100 removed is
1-0.609
2-0.450
3-0.515
4-0.000
5-0.389
6-0.518
7-0.475
8-0.475

so far i have replaced u6101 and u1900. removed j6100

Not sure where to go from here.

title: 820-00165-a fan spin, no chime, no display
message: Originally i replaced the same chip after cleaning pin 7, when that had the result i described above i replaced with another from the same model 820-00165-a donor. Same result

title: 820-00165-a fan spin, no chime, no display
message: At least put back original chip and check all resistors in serie with data lines R6110 and up 18 of them. Also the traces between them.

title: 820-00165-a fan spin, no chime, no display
message: Replaced original u6100, checked all resistors between r6110 and r6133, all fine, traces between them have 0.000v voltage drop along them, only traces to smc and cpu i could not measure

title: 820-00165-a fan spin, no chime, no display
message: Pin 8 of U1950 corroded? Was there crap around U1900?

title: 820-00165-a fan spin, no chime, no display
message: pulled and checked u1950, looks fine, liquid didn't look to make it as far as u1900 but i pulled and replaced anyway.

title: 820-00165-a fan spin, no chime, no display
message: Out of ideas. Check all resistors and traces to U6100 again, there are 20 or so of them in that circuit.
